LISTERIOSIS - MACEDONIA: (KUMANOVO) FATAL, PORK MEAT PRODUCT ALERT, RECALL
**************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Thu 7 Aug 2014
Source: Focus News Agency [edited]
http://www.focus-fen.net/news/2014/08/07/344928/utrinski-vesnik-macedonia-source-of-listeria-bacteria-found.html


[The] source of _Listeria_ bacteria [has been] found. Smoked blade shoulder pork produced by a firm called "Ekstra Mein" in Kumanovo [Macedonia] is most probably the source of _Listeria_ bacteria in Macedonia, which infected 8 people, 4 of whom died, the Macedonian online news edition Utrinski Vesnik reported.

The contagious diseases commission with the ministry of health said the _Listeria_ found were of the same prototype the 8 people were infected with. Yesterday [6 Aug 2014] it was announced that a 5th person had died of listeriosis in Macedonia.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

******
[2]
Date: Thu 7 Aug 2014
Source: Republika [summ., edited]
http://english.republika.mk/?p=126479


A sample of smoked pork neck slices, product of Kumanovo company 'Extra Mein', has tested positive for the presence of _Listeria_ bacteria, which is a 98 percent match with the bacteria genotype found in 8 patients in Macedonia, 4 of whom have died.

This is a serious direction for locating the source of the disease. Relevant institutions should now make epidemiological tests and take further measures for following the chain of the disease outbreak, Zvonko Milenkovic, chair of the Commission for Infectious Disease at the Ministry of Health, told reporters on Wednesday [6 Aug 2014].

Director of the Food and Veterinary Dejan Runtevski said all of the smoked pork neck slices products would be withdrawn from retail sale by the end of the day. An order has been also issued for putting the production on hold, which will enable testing of samples taken from the working places, machines, and anywhere that this bacterium may be present, Runtevski said. All products that are to be distributed to markets will be also tested, he added.

--
