******
[3]
Date: Thu 7 Aug 2014
Source: Republika [edited]
http://english.republika.mk/?p=126524


Potentially _Listeria_ contaminated products of 'Ekstra Mein' meat industry have been recalled Wednesday [6 Aug 2014], after Health Ministry and Food and Veterinary Agency detected _Listeria_ presence in smoked pork neck slices.

Meanwhile, Food and Veterinary Agency recommends for citizens to stop consuming Ekstra Mein's product 'smoked pork neck slices', lots 07632 and 07633, produced at 21.07.2014 and best before 04.09.2014.

The Food and Veterinary Agency is working toward detection of the _Listeria_ source, conducting further tests and analyses.

As of 30 Jul 2014, the Agency implements extremely strict control of all lots of animal source food to prevent, decrease, and eliminate the risk of _Listeria_ [contamination].

