******
[4]
Date: Thu 7 Aug 2014
Source: Independent [edited]
http://www.independent.mk/articles/8098/Ekstra+Mein+No+Listeria+at+Our+Premises,+We+Will+Ask+For+Supernalysis%22


[Telegraf.mk reports that in response to findings that their product vacuum pork neck, is the cause of the listeriosis that infected 9 people and killed 4 of them, the company "Ekstra Mein" from Kumanovo, said all their products, including the sliced pork neck, are thermally treated at a temperature of 73-79 deg C [163.4-174.2 deg F], which guarantees destruction of the bacteria _Listeria_.]

The company claims that since the beginning of the year [2014], according to a regular plan for sampling, 158 samples were taken from 112 products and swabs (69 of desktops and machines and 43 of workers). All obtained results were negative to the presence of any bacteria.

"It is impossible for thermally unprocessed product to exit our company. All products, including the sliced pork neck are thermally treated at a temperature of 73-79 deg C [163.4-174.2 deg F], which guarantees destruction of the bacteria _Listeria_. Additionally, the company is subject to constant quality controls of the products. We have a regular plan of test sampling of the finished product in accordance with legal regulations, a regular plan for taking swabs, as well as our own control system using a device that detects the presence of organic matter. The 3 extraordinary controls in our factory in the past 10 days by the Food and Veterinary Agency and the Ministry of Health of the overall HACCP [Hazard Analysis and Critical Control Points]-documentation and hygiene-technical norms at the facility showed no irregularities. All samples and swabs taken from "Ekstra Mein" were negative," the statement said.

The company will require superanalysis of this product (for the isolate as well as the typization) from the Food and Veterinary Agency, which should be made in world-renowned institution.

"Ekstra Mein" management also [points out] the fact that the sample with bacteria was found in products in retail shops, so the company cannot guarantee how the products were kept, if loss of vacuum was possible and, if that was the case, whether they came in contact with other products that contain bacteria.

