[A detailed discussion of listeriosis can be found in ProMED-mail archive no 20071230.4186.

In the US, _Listeria monocytogenes_ isolates, usually from blood, cerebrospinal fluid, tissue from a normally sterile site, or products of conception (such as amniotic fluid, placental, or fetal tissue), are forwarded to state public health laboratories for pulsed field gel electrophoresis (PFGE) subtyping, the results of which are submitted to PulseNet, the National Molecular Subtyping Network for Foodborne Disease Surveillance, to identify clusters of possibly related cases. When PulseNet identifies a cluster of _L. monocytogenes_ patient isolates with the same molecular pattern, epidemiologists conduct a preliminary case-control analysis by comparing responses to food exposures reported on the Listeria Case Report from patients in the cluster to those from patients outside the cluster (http://www.cdc.gov/listeria/surveillance.html).

Presumably, what the 1st news report refers to as the "prototype" may be the molecular pattern found on PFGE of _L. monocytogenes_ strains. If so, the news report is saying that all 8 patients had the same "prototype" (that is, PFGE subtype), suggesting a common source, and the "prototype" of the strains isolated from the 8 patients is the same as the "prototype" of the strain isolated from the suspected food source (smoked pork). However, the manufacturer of the pork meat product contends that contamination with _L. monocytogenes_ occurred after the product left their facility.

Maps of Macedonia can be seen at http://www.ezilon.com/maps/images/europe/Macedonian-political-map.gif and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2670279,40862.

Kumanovo is a city, with a population of 70 842 in 2002, and municipality in the Northeastern Statistical Region, 1 of 8 statistical regions in the Republic of Macedonia (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kumanovo). For a map of Macedonia showing the location of Kumanovo Municipality, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northeastern_statistical_region#mediaviewer/File:Map_of_the_municipalities_of_the_Northeastern_Statistical_Region_en.svg. - Mod.ML]
